The paper discusses a model for electing a group of representatives, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of different multi-winner election rules suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The consideration of voters' preferences and satisfaction implies a focus on data science (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
